## 9. Interpretation

**Explanation A (Informational Advantage):** The low-snare group reflects
constraints where non-institutional observers partially agree with the
institutional rope classification, suggesting the institution may have
genuine insight. Evidence for A: different orbit signatures, non-institutional
observers seeing tangled_rope rather than snare.

**Explanation B (Metric Bias):** The low-snare group simply has lower
extractiveness/suppression/theater metrics, which mechanically reduces
P(snare). Evidence for B: strong rank-biserial correlations on extraction
metrics, similar orbit structures between groups.
